<TITLE> UZ polls on one day: Sakhawat </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 2 (bdnews24.com)  Election commissioner M Sakhawat Hossain has said the EC is planning to hold the nationwide 481 upazila elections in one go on the same day instead of on two separate dates as previously announced. He told bdnews24.com at his office on Sunday evening: "Upazila elections will succeed the parliamentary election and will be held in December." He said the probable date would be Dec 28. Chief election commissioner ATM Shamsul Huda will announce the election schedules at 7:30 pm in a televised speech. The last upazila polls were held on March 24 & 25 in 1990. The first such election of the country took place on May 16-20 in 1985. bd
